 {"id":"bd-pm-2","title":"PORT: proc_maps sub-bead 2 \u2014 rewire abi callers","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","epic":"bd-pm-epic","created_at":"2026-04-24T22:05:20.017352Z","description":"Replace inline parse_maps_line in host_resolve.rs with a call to core::proc_maps::parse_maps_line, then apply the libc.so + r--p + offset==0 filter on the returned MapsEntry. Replace pthread_abi.rs::parse_maps_range with a call to core::proc_maps::parse_maps_range. Verify both abi tests still pass.","updated_at":"2026-04-24T22:07:17.699830Z","created_by":"cod-frankenlibc","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"closed_at":"2026-04-24T22:07:17.699830Z","close_reason":"host_resolve.rs::parse_maps_line shrinks from ~25 to ~16 lines: it now delegates to core::proc_maps::parse_maps_line, then applies the libc.so + r--p + offset==0 filter on the returned MapsEntry. pthread_abi.rs::parse_maps_range becomes a 1-line forwarder. Both abi callers retain their specific filtering / output-shape logic at the boundary. 173/173 abi lib tests pass."}
