-{"id": "bd-wcv-epic", "title": "PORT: wcstol/wcstoul wide-char number parsing to core::stdlib::conversion", "status": "open", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "epic", "created_at": "2026-04-25T00:54:12.807307Z", "description": "wchar_abi.rs duplicates ~180 lines of base/sign/prefix/digit-accumulation logic that already lives in core::stdlib::conversion::strtol_impl / strtoul_impl, but on &[u32] instead of &[u8]. Plus three local helpers (wide_is_space, wide_digit_value, wide_is_ascii_hexdigit) replicate stdlib utilities. Lift the wide variants into core::stdlib::conversion alongside the byte versions, sharing the existing ConversionStatus enum."}
