-{"id": "bd-wcv-1", "title": "PORT: wcstol/wcstoul sub-bead 1 \u2014 core wide-char number parsers", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "task", "epic": "bd-wcv-epic", "closed_at": "2026-04-25T00:59:40.135727Z", "resolution": "Added to core::stdlib::conversion: pub fn wide_is_space(wc: u32) -> bool (Unicode-aware whitespace recognition via char::from_u32().is_whitespace()); pub fn wide_digit_value(wc: u32) -> Option<u32> (matches strtol digit-table semantics for ASCII 0-9/a-z/A-Z); pub fn wcstol_impl(s: &[u32], base: i32) -> (i64, usize, ConversionStatus) and pub fn wcstoul_impl structurally identical to the byte-slice strtol_impl/strtoul_impl. All four share the existing ConversionStatus enum (no duplication). 31 unit tests cover Unicode whitespace recognition, digit-value mapping, base 0 auto-detect (0x->16, 0->8, else 10), explicit base 16 + 0x prefix, base 2..=36 validation, sign-only/empty/whitespace-only edge cases, overflow/underflow status reporting, mid-digit base mismatch, plus 3 parity tests proving wcstol_impl/wcstoul_impl produce IDENTICAL (value, consumed, status) tuples vs strtol_impl/strtoul_impl on ASCII inputs across a dozen cases including i64::MAX/MIN, u64::MAX/overflow, base 0/16/36/8."}
